document_data.History:
Marlin Stormserpent brought Thirsty to [[Castle Obarskyr]] in [[Suzail]], hidden within his jerkin, when he came with a retinue to steal the ''[[Wyverntongue Chalice]]'' under cover of darkness.{{cite book/Elminster Must Die/MMP|81|7}} During the one skirmish they had with [[Purple Dragon knight]]s on patrol, Thirsty was instrumental in paralyzing the one who split out from the group to summon reinforcements.{{cite book/Elminster Must Die/MMP|127-131|12}}

Marlin again hid Thirsty in his jerkin when meeting the city watch later, the day he was informed of [[Gaskur]]'s murder, though he did not ultimately call on it.{{cite book/Elminster Must Die/MMP|303|29}}

Thirsty was later eliminated by [[Mirt]] after it tried to attack him as the man entered the Royal Palace of Suzail.{{cite book/Elminster Must Die/MMP|355-356|34}} Before the killing, Mirt had been last seen escaping out of [[Stormserpent Towers]], where he had an altercation with Marlin and his co-conspirators after Marlin had realized he was not a blueflame ghost.
